<div id="p501" class="blockpost rowodd firstpost">
	<h2><span><span class="conr">#1&nbsp;</span><a href="viewtopic.php?pid=501#p501">2008-09-12 13:22:45</a></span></h2>
	<div class="box">
		<div class="inbox">
			<div class="postleft">
				<dl>
					<dt><strong><a href="profile.php?id=90022">sren</a></strong></dt>
					<dd class="usertitle"><strong>Member</strong></dd>
					<dd class="postavatar"></dd>
				</dl>
			</div>
			<div class="postright">
				<h3>Top-BT: a BT client to speed downloading twice with less traffic</h3>
				<div class="postmsg">
					<p>Hi,<br /><br />We are researchers at the Ohio State University. We have implemented and released a new BitTorrent client software based on Vuze, called TopBT. Different from previously released BT client, Top-BT actively discovers Internet topology, and uses this intelligence to always choose close peers to download file pieces. Our study shows that, TopBT can save significant amount of BitTorrent traffic at the same time maintaining moderate download speed.<br /><br />You all are very welcome to try out our Top-BT client, and give us some advice, suggestions, and comments. Currently the Top-BT client can be downloaded from two places:<br /><br /><a href="http://sourceforge.net/projects/top-bt/" rel="nofollow">http://sourceforge.net/projects/top-bt/</a><br /><a href="http://www.cse.ohio-state.edu/~sren/topbt/" rel="nofollow">http://www.cse.ohio-state.edu/~sren/topbt/</a><br /><br />Regards,<br />Shansi</p>
					<p class="postedit"><em>Last edited by sren (2009-01-23 01:47:03)</em></p>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="clearer"></div>
			<div class="postfootleft"><p>Offline</p></div>
			<div class="postfootright"><div>&nbsp;</div></div>
		</div>
	</div>
